[Socialist Union of Popular Forces]]. Between 2007 and 2012, he held the position of Minister of Industry, Trade and New Technologies in the [[Cabinet of Morocco|cabinet]] of [[Abbas El Fassi]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Nadia DREF|title=Ahmed Chami prim\u00e9|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/lematin/2816|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=Le Matin|date=2007-02-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Le plan de bataille d'Ahmed Chami|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/letemps/18649|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=Le temps|date=2009-12-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Ahmed R\u00e9da Chami : Cart\u00e9sien\u2026pragmatique|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/lagazette/19056|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=La Gazette du Maroc|date=2009-01-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Investissement : Hassan Bernoussi sous la coupe de Ahmed Chami|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/challenge/124|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=Challenge hebdo|date=2007-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Imane Bouhrara|title=Ahmed Reda Chami, un ministre branch\u00e9 Net|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/financesnews/7042|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=Finances news|date=2010-02-04}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, he was appointed by the king of Morocco in the Special Committee on Model of Development.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mapnews.ma/en/activites-royales/composition-special-committee-model-development|title=Composition of Special Committee on Model of Development {{!}} MapNews|website=www.mapnews.ma|access-date=2020-02-14}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Cabinet of Morocco]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://twitter.com/Ahmed_R_Chami Official Twitter account]\n\n{{Cabinet of Abbas El Fassi}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chami, Ahmed}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Morocco]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:People from Casablanca]]\n[[Category:Moroccan businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Moroccan engineers]]\n\n\n{{Morocco-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific-prefix   = \n|name               = Ahmed Chami\n|honorific-suffix   = \n|image              = Ahmed Reda Chami - World Economic Forum on the Middle East 2010.jpg\n|imagesize          = 190px\n|smallimage         = <!--If this is specified, \"image\" should not be.-->\n|alt                = \n|caption            = \n|order              = \n<!-----office------------>\n|office            = Member of Parliament for [[Fes]]\n|term_start        = 3 January 2012\n|term_end          = \n|predecessor       = \n|successor        = \n<!-----office1----->\n|office1             = Minister of Industry, Trade and New Technologies\n|term_start1         = 19 September 2007\n|term_end1           = 3 January 2012\n|monarch1            = [[Mohammed VI]]\n|primeminister1      = [[Abbas El Fassi]]\n|predecessor1        = [[Salaheddine Mezouar]]\n|successor1         = [[Abdelkader Aamara]]\n\n<!------------------------------------data---->\n|party              = [[Socialist Union of Popular Forces|USFP]]\n|birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1961|5|16}}\n|birth_place        = [[Casablanca]], [[Morocco]]\n|death_date         = \n|death_place        = \n|restingplace       = \n|restingplacecoordinates = \n|birthname          = \n|citizenship        = \n|nationality        = \n|spouse             = \n|relations          = \n|children           = \n|residence          = \n|alma_mater         = [[\u00c9cole centrale Paris]]\n|occupation         = Politician, businessman, engineer\n|profession         = \n|cabinet            = \n|committees         = \n|portfolio          = \n|religion           = [[Sunni Islam]]\n|signature          = \n|signature_alt      = \n|website            = \n|footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Ahmed Chami''' sometimes '''Ahmed Reda Chami''' ({{lang-ar|\u0623\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0627\u0645\u064a}} &ndash; born 16 May 1961, [[Casablanca]]) is a Moroccan politician of the [[Socialist Union of Popular Forces]]. Between 2007 and 2012, he held the position of Minister of Industry, Trade and New Technologies in the [[Cabinet of Morocco|cabinet]] of [[Abbas El Fassi]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Nadia DREF|title=Ahmed Chami prim\u00e9|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/lematin/2816|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=Le Matin|date=2007-02-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Le plan de bataille d'Ahmed Chami|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/letemps/18649|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=Le temps|date=2009-12-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Ahmed R\u00e9da Chami : Cart\u00e9sien\u2026pragmatique|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/lagazette/19056|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=La Gazette du Maroc|date=2009-01-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Investissement : Hassan Bernoussi sous la coupe de Ahmed Chami|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/challenge/124|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=Challenge hebdo|date=2007-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Imane Bouhrara|title=Ahmed Reda Chami, un ministre branch\u00e9 Net|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/financesnews/7042|accessdate=14 August 2012|newspaper=Finances news|date=2010-02-04}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, he was appointed by the king of morocco in the Special Committee on Model of Development.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mapnews.ma/en/activites-royales/composition-special-committee-model-development|title=Composition of Special Committee on Model of Development {{!}} MapNews|website=www.mapnews.ma|access-date=2020-02-14}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Cabinet of Morocco]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://twitter.com/Ahmed_R_Chami Official Twitter account]\n\n{{Cabinet of Abbas El Fassi}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chami, Ahmed}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Morocco]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:People from Casablanca]]\n[[Category:Moroccan businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Moroccan engineers]]\n\n\n{{Morocco-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user":